description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen within the Emergency Surgery and Elective Care Business unit on the Orthopaedic Unit Wansbeck General Hospital. The unit comprises a 22-bed elective ward, 6 bed Bone and Joint Infection Unit and a 4 bed Surgical Enhanced Recovery Unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit enthusiastic, well-motivated Registered Nurses to join our team on the Orthopaedic Unit. This busy unit strives to deliver high quality, holistic care to all our patients. We pride ourselves on the adaptability of our team to meet the challenges that Orthopaedic Nursing brings. Within orthopaedics there are huge opportunities to learn and develop skills at all levels.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We actively encourage our staff to develop their skills through a variety of learning environments, this will not only be beneficial to the patients care but give an individual a sense of ownership and team development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be expected to provide high standards of care to those patients accessing our services. You should demonstrate excellent communication skills, and have a flexible approach to your work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Essential Criteria:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1st Level live NMC registered Nurse&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentorship qualification or relevant qualification (essential requirement for post, expectation this will be completed within an 18 month period)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be flexible to meet the needs of the service and be able to work a full variety of shifts including days and night&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Claire Stockhill&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ward Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;claire.stockhill@northumbria-healthcare.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;01670 529107&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date: 16th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
